cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.CY, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper proposes an anonymous communication scheme with integrity protection and privacy, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on vehicular ad hoc networks (VANETs) and proposes a communication scheme for vehicles to connect and communicate with each other, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a certificateless ring signature to reduce the length of the signature and simplify the key management, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the privacy and auditability aspects of the proposed scheme, which falls under the scope of computers and society.
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper presents a small-scale implementation to show the availability of the prototype system, which falls under the scope of software engineering.
